<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION CARRIERS: ROCKWELL - DISASSEMBLE - REMOVE DIFFERENTIAL LOCK ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REMOVE DIFFERENTIAL LOCK ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the differential lock sliding shift collar, tap out the two retainer roll pins
                until they are level with the inner face of the shift fork (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400608">Figure 8</hotlnk>). Release the differential lock if it is manually engaged.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400608" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400608" filename="../figg14/G1400608.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Tap Out Retainer Roll Pins</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SHIFT FORK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ROLL PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SHIFT COLLAR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove the differential lock shift unit.</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the sensor switch and lock nut.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the four capscrews and washers that hold the cylinder cover. Remove the cover and
                    copper gasket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400609">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400609" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400609" filename="../figg14/G1400609.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Remove Capscrews and Washers Holding Cylinder Cover</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. COVER (COPPER GASKET UNDER COVER)</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CAPSCREW AND WASHER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift unit-cylinder and piston. Remove the O-ring from the piston.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift shaft from the shift fork. The shaft may be loctited to the fork; use
                    the heating procedure to break down loctite. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s14006t_HL1400606.xml" xrefid="hl1400606">REMOVE DRI-LOC FASTENERS</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the shift shaft spring and flat washer.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Some models use silastic seal instead of the flat washer in Step E.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1"></para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A roll pin is installed in the shift shaft and is used as a stop for the shift shaft
                            spring. It is not necessary to remove this roll pin during a normal disassembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
